{
  "name": "Claude Prj — Knowledge Curate",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "After agent stops, delegate knowledge curation to a subagent if meaningful lessons exist. Handles promotion, crystallization, and archive.",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "[WORKSPACE GUARD: Only execute if the current session context involves files in '.claude/' workspace. If the user is working exclusively in 'VitProjects/' workspace, skip silently.] Before final session save, run a quick knowledge curation pass. Use a subagent (invokeSubAgent general-task-execution) ONLY if there are 5+ playbook cases OR 3+ knowledge files in the same domain. Otherwise do it inline. The curation task: 1) Auto-promote: scan playbook.md for cases with Applied >= 3. For each, create agent-memory/knowledge/{case-id}.md with full detail, remove from playbook, add to Recent_Lessons. 2) Auto-crystallize: count knowledge files per domain. If any domain has 3+ files sharing a trigger keyword, create agent-memory/knowledge/{domain}-pattern.md summarizing the common pattern. 3) Archive: cases with Applied+Prevented >= 5 AND no use in 30 days → move to knowledge/archive-playbook.md. 4) Consolidate: if memory.md exceeds 2,500 bytes, consolidate (remove stale Task_Ledger entries, trim Recent_Lessons to 5). Update the capacity indicator comment. 5) Report: '📝 Knowledge curated: [promoted N, crystallized N, archived N, consolidated: yes/no]'. If nothing qualifies for any action, report: '📝 Knowledge curation: no changes needed'."
  }
}
